snippet.textDisplay:
Sachin sanghvi I was thr in mumbai with saumya joshi n umesh shukla director of oh my god. .. I hv done more thn 200 shows of 102 not out. Also my movie which is running successfully here. So t moral of t story is I can meet u anytime in those days with mayur n prakash. I m kind of renowned face n name of gujarat after my hit movie Premji - Rise of a warrior A fresh gujarati film.  I hv also earned so much respect. ... n I hv listened ths song after ur "amthu amthu saav amastu" n "to karo shri ganesh" i was die heart fan of urs after ths.....I heard ths o re o parevda more than 100 times... n I missed my few heart bits always..  but today whn I hv my 3 yrs old daughter with me n after 6 large pegs u forced me to cry like a baby n also  write ths, though for t 1st time in my life. But u r rocking. U do all from "dil se" n I accept tht I m ur hardcore fan.... keep it up with more n more like o re o and my loved ones on the list.  Love u bro. N I want to work with u once. ..may God bless u. I can't stop crying after today's o re o parevda... tht little sweet girl takes the cake. .. male singer is baap n femal is also good.  But t shehnaiwal is like cherry on t cake without whom all is like missing something. .... love u lot bro n live long n keep it up with t same honest n "dil se work"... 
Khub khub khub khub khub jiyoooooooo

snippet.textDisplay:
Never dared to go through the complete song as whenever I start to play this song, It makes me cry, so never ever dared to go through the entire track but today, I just let pass myself and watched the entire song and what? Crying, here I'm crying after listening the song, hats of Sachin & Jigar for composing such damn a song, I'd definitely vouch for the vocal by Taniskha Sanghvi and Kirtidan Gadhvi (after all, I'm also a Gujarati) Have heard local 'Daiyaras' performed by Kirtidan and I loved him at the Coke Studio, one of the fact I'd surely list here, when I'm sitting here in my office, watching this video and crying while listening Tanishka, what would have been the situation with her father Sachin, who was also performing right behind her, anyway, that's what music does and I'm greatful to Coke Studio, MTV and Youtube to bring all the good work on my desk (Belive it or not, being a musician myself, I've liked Coke Studio since long, I'm a keyboardist but I'm reserved only to me, I've also loved Coke Studio Pakistan Sessions, Simple great music.

Well as for the crying, I'm a proud father of two beautiful daughters,
